draw(xscale(sqrt(3))*yscale(sqrt(6))*Circle((0,0),1));
draw((sqrt(2),sqrt(2))--(-sqrt(2),sqrt(2))--(-sqrt(2),-sqrt(2))--(sqrt(2),-sqrt(2))--cycle);
draw((-2,0)--(2,0));
draw((0,-3)--(0,3));
draw((0,0)--(sqrt(3),0));
draw((0,0)--(0,sqrt(6)));
[/asy]

Hence, the area of the square is $\left( \min(\sqrt{3},\sqrt{6}) \right)^2 = \boxed{3}.$
